5461	  The basic open \(D(f) \subseteq \operatorname{Spec} R\) is an affine scheme, and the
5462	  canonical comparison \(D(f) \cong \operatorname{Spec} R_f\) is an isomorphism of affine
5463	  schemes (it corresponds to the localisation ring map \(R \to R_f\)). Pulling the restricted
5464	  module \(\mathcal{F}|_{D(f)}\) back along the inverse of this isomorphism transports it to a
5465	  sheaf of \(\mathcal{O}_{\operatorname{Spec} R_f}\)-modules \(\mathcal{F}_{(f)}\); the unit of
5466	  the transport supplies the comparison isomorphism. Restriction of sheaves of modules and
5467	  pullback along an isomorphism are both functorial, so the assignment
5468	  \(\mathcal{F} \mapsto \mathcal{F}_{(f)}\) is functorial in \(\mathcal{F}\).
5469	\end{proof}
